            "style": "",
            "text": "‚ÄúToday‚Äôs federal court decision ordering Starbucks to reinstate the seven unlawfully fired Starbucks workers in Memphis is a crucial step in ensuring that these workers, and all Starbucks workers, can freely exercise their right to join together to improve their working conditions and form a union,‚Äù said NLRB General Counsel Jennifer Abruzzo in statement. ‚ÄúStarbucks, and other employers, should take note that the NLRB will continue to vigorously protect workers‚Äô right to organize without interference from their employer.‚Äù",
